<br>
I was baptised a methodist, by a mother who was mormon, and a father who was a universalist. Religion was not a big part of my formative years, but it was there, I was exposed to it.<br>
  I'm a direct descendant of Roger Conant, the 1st governor of Massachusetts Bay Colony, and I believe they were Puritans, who were driven out of England for thier religious beliefs, and were as intolerant a lot of people as any Muslim Fundamentalist. They burned &quot;witches&quot; at Salem. I married a woman who thinks she may be Jewish. ( she has the stereotypical big nose), but my son isn't circumcised.<br>
<br>
I believe what I believe, not sure what you would call it. Sort of descended from Richard Bach's &quot;Illusion&quot; and &quot;One&quot;, with a little bit of Christian History thrown in. I say &quot;history&quot;, because I believe that Christ the historical figure probably existed. Not too sure about the status as &quot;Son of God&quot; put upon him by early Romans. Richard Bach also explains that pretty well. I can't be an atheist, because as I look out my window at the Elementary school playground, it just seems too improbable that this was all a cosmic accident. <br>
This may be kind of rambly and incoherent...<br>
<br>
