No they didn't. No witches were ever burned in America, that was a European practice. In America, we hanged them.<br>
<br>
I might also add that while individual Puritans were to blame for the Salem witch trials, Puritan society was not. Puritan law would not have permitted the Salem trials to occur, because it required a much higher threshold of  evidence and witness testimony -- the same act had to be witnessed by two people, testimony from torture was deemed unreliable, etc. For example, in the only recorded case of &quot;ducking&quot; was at the request of the accused, who apparently felt that she would be exonerated. In that case, the ducking showed her to be guilty of witchcraft, but the Puritan authorities refused to consider it as evidence because it was based on superstition, and so she was eventually exonerated.<br>
<br>
The Salem witch trials were the result of a change in the colonial government. James II was sick of the way these religious radicals were running the show, so the Massachusetts charter was revoked in 1680-something or other (too lazy to look it up) and a non-Puritan governor was appointed. The Salem witch trials took place under English law, not under Puritan law. <br>
<br>
When we look at the numbers, they show just how hard it was to get a witchcraft conviction under Puritan courts. Before the charter was revoked, the conviction rate was somewhere under 25% (again, too lazy to look up the exact number), whereas on the European continent it was over 50%.<br>
<br>
So, to re-cap: No burning of witches in America, and if anyone is to blame for the Salem witch trials it is not Puritan law -- though obviously individual Puritans were involved in the accusations and enforcement of English law. <br>
<br>
Hug a Puritan today!<br>
<br>
Yours,<br>
Gnosis Bunglefoot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujebbar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jebbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/19/02 4:40:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=95>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hm</span><hr size=1> Oh! I forgot to mention I was a devout Jehovah's Witness for the first 17 years of my life. I seem to be unique in that sense :P<br>
